prompt:
Write a brief summary about an important historical figure and his or her significant achievements.
George Washington was a pivotal figure in American history who served as the first president of the United States from 1789 to 1797, during which he oversaw the creation of a strong central government and established precedents that have shaped the country's political system ever since. Washington played a critical role in the American Revolution against Britain, serving as commander-in-chief of the Continental Army from 1775 to 1783, leading it to victory over British forces at Yorktown in 1781. He was later elected president of the Confederation Congress from 1785 to 1788, where he helped draft and ratify the United States Constitution.
